carried live on ESPN and began by telling the sports world that he
was done coaching. ``This time,'' he said, ``it's final and
forever.'' Ten minutes later, he waved goodbye, hopped in his black
Corvette and came here, a town in the Keys that says goodbye to
visitors with a sign that says, ``Catch you later!'' Funny, but
eight months later, he hasn't let anybody catch him. At least not
anybody outside his close circle of friends and family. (Woods,
Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
