   DANCE-FEST (Undated) _ Liz Thompson talks about her new
``Evening Stars'' dance festival. By Jennifer Dunning.
</P>
<P>
   COE-RACIST-MUSIC (Undated) _ In the early '80s, the outlaw
country singer David Allan Coe released in very small quantities
two underground albums of songs that are among the most racist,
misogynist, homophobic and obscene songs ever recorded by a popular
songwriter. Bootlegged by fans and college fraternity members for
years, those songs have recently been stirring up new trouble on
the Internet. Now Coe, who has long since distanced himself from
the music and been toning down his act for a new record deal, has
decided to start making money off the music. By Neil Strauss.
</P>
<P>
   LITTLE-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ Maureen Corrigan reviews ``It's
the Little Things,'' by Lena Williams.
</P>
