<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ It seems crystal clear from here.
But Max Shauck's machines are having a fit. We are looking down at
the face of oil refining on Texas' coast. Aside bulbous, pale
storage tanks, heater and boiler stacks reach to the sky. From here
they are like many whiskers on many moles. Shauck's DeHavilland
Twin Otter is making loops at up to 5,000 feet over Galveston Bay
and the Houston Ship Channel, sampling air pollution. (Young, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   EZZARD-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ On a 90-degree day in a downtown
parking lot last week, the surface temperature of a parked
automobile measured 150 degrees. On hot summer days, parked cars
emit hydrocarbons that add to ozone pollution, just like cars stuck
in traffic jams do. (Ezzard, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
