<P>
   FOOD-OWEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ ``Remember a few years ago when you
ran a recipe for cracked goat shins?'' a reader is liable to write.
Chances are I don't remember and my only excuse is that I have
passed on approximately 3,800 recipes since this column was
hatched. Richard Sieger swears he has read most of them and
suggests that I republish some of the best recipes. What he
specifically had in mind were three chicken-wing marinades first
published about 30 years ago.
</P>
<P>
   By John Owen. (Story has moved in the ``l'' category.)
