<HEADLINE>
THE FUTURE OF SPORTSBARS?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The first true Webcast of a football game had its expected
glitches _ mostly caused because of the volume of users _ but the
otherwise successful venture by FoxSports.com in carrying
Saturday's Nebraska-San Jose State game at least established a
beginning point.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's emerging technology,'' said Danny Greenberg, senior vice
president of FoxSports.com. ``It is not perfect yet. It will
continue to improve.''
</P>
<P>
   The game was nowhere on TV, so sports bars in Nebraska did the
next best thing, putting the Webcast onto TV screens.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's better than listening to it on the radio,'' customer Tim
Goodman, who sat at DJ's Dugout bar in Omaha, sporting a Nebraska
jersey, told the Associated Press. ``It is a little delayed, but
it's good.''
</P>
<P>
   Those wishing to sample the proceedings can click onto the Web
site and hear it on demand. A 56K modem and video-streaming
software are needed.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Yahoo announced last week that it signed an agreement
with three sports-marketing and Web-development organizations to
provide live Webcasts of football and other sports for 22 colleges,
including Alabama, Colorado, Georgia, Indiana and Michigan.
</P>
<P>
   -- It's no fun being Joe Paterno these days, even if you do have
your own new Web site.
</P>
<P>
   The coaching resource named CoachPaterno.com has links to
clinics, drills, officiating news and even motivational speeches.
Among other college coaches participating in the site are BYU's
LaVell Edwards, Purdue's Joe Tiller, Arizona's Dick Tomey,
Illinois' Ron Turner, Missouri's Larry Smith, Oregon's Mike
Bellotti, Washington's Rick Neuheisel and San Diego State's Ted
Tollner.
</P>
<P>
   -- Michelle Marciniak of the Portland Fire ended up winning the
Playboy.com poll of the ``Sexiest Babe of the WNBA,'' taking nearly
44 percent of the 50,000 votes cast. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
