<HEADLINE>
CARD DEALERS READY FOR SOME FOOTBALL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Rob Veres admits he's ``stoked'' the NFL season's
finally here.
</P>
<P>
   OK, so he does have some financial stake in it.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a real changing of the guard in the hobby,'' said the
owner of Burbank Sportscards. ``Where the guys like Elway, Marino,
Young, Rice dominated the last 10 years, now it's Peyton Manning,
Kurt Warner, Peter Warrick, Plaxico Burress, Daunte Culpepper,
Jamal Lewis, even LaVar Arrington, and he's a defensive player ...
the emphasis has switched in a hurry.''
</P>
<P>
   Card collectors show their excitement by how much they spend. So
far, Veres says NFL card sales both at his store and his Web site
(www.burbanksportscards.com) have been brisk in anticipation of
who'll turn out to be the new hot commodity.
</P>
<P>
   With more than a half-dozen companies spitting out the shiny
cardboard in 2000, there's a need to separate the must-have from
the don't-bother. Veres breaks down his top five choices for the
best and brightest packs of cards for serious collectors (concerned
more with quality) as well as for the kids (who look to get more
for their money): &QL; 
SERIOUS COLLECTORS:
</P>
<P>
   1. Upper Deck Pros and Prospects ($9 for 5 cards). ``These are
flying off the shelves,'' said Veres. ``The Warrick card is already
at $350, and Arrington is $100.''
</P>
<P>
   2. Donruss Elite ($7 for 5 cards).
</P>
<P>
   3. Topps Chrome ($4 for 4 cards).
</P>
<P>
   4. Playoff Prestige ($7 for 4 cards). New feature insert are
swatch cards from rookie's college alma maters.
</P>
<P>
   5. Crown Royale ($6 for 6 cards), featuring the crown-shaped die
cut that ``still is very much a fringe card,'' said Veres. &QL; 
KIDS:
</P>
<P>
   1. Upper Deck MVP ($2 for 10 cards). Offers the best chance at
valuable insert cards.
</P>
<P>
   2. Impact ($1 for 10 cards). Don't underestimate the team-logo
tattoos.
</P>
<P>
   3. Victory ($1 for 12 cards).
</P>
<P>
   4. Topps ($1.50 for 10 cards). Always a good seller in any
sport, with a neat reproduction series of Johnny Unitas cards.
</P>
<P>
   5. Sky Box Dominions ($1.50 for 10 cards). &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
