<HEADLINE>
AN NFL TOP TEN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Ten earthshaking developments for this NFL season, based on
seismic activity from Week 1:
</P>
<P>
   1. Danny Snyder will have overpaid.
</P>
<P>
   2. Ryan Leaf won't have the patience to last past Week 3.
</P>
<P>
   3. Troy Aikman won't have enough marbles left to survive past
Week 2.
</P>
<P>
   4. Cade McNown comparisons to Steve Young won't be too
ridiculous.
</P>
<P>
   5. ``Culpepper to Kleinsasser'' won't cut it. ``Culpepper on a
keeper'' might.
</P>
<P>
   6. Neil O'Donnell won't look so bad to P'burgh. But then,
neither does Terry Hanratty.
</P>
