   -- Before the Dodgers yanked him up from Double-A San Antonio
for the final month of the season, Australia native Luke Prokopec
was all pumped up to go home to pitch for his boys in the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
   How bad would it have looked if he beat Tommy Lasorda's kids
Down Under in a gold-medal game? ...
</P>
<P>
   -- Number of former, current and future UCLA athletes and
coaches representing the U.S. and six foreign countries in Sydney:
56. ...
</P>
<P>
   -- Serena and Venus can wear whatever they darn please. ...
</P>
<P>
   -- Carver High, coach Reeves, Salami, Coolidge, Haywood ... and
ESPN Classic.
</P>
<P>
   Starting this morning, ``The White Shadow'' will make the
weekday lineup on the ESPN sister channel _ another reason to call
your cable operator and scream for it if it's not dialed in by
now. &QL; 
